Sentencas: Double perovslcites LnBaCo(2)O(5+delta) (Ln = rare earth) are explored as cathode materials for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cell.
Titulo: NdBaCo2/3Fe2/3Cu2/3O5+δ double perovskite as a novel cathode material for CeO2- and LaGaO3-based solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Barriers to the applicability of double perovskite cathodes include high thermal expansion coefficient (TEC) and poor chemical compatibility with common electrolytes.
Titulo: NdBaCo2/3Fe2/3Cu2/3O5+δ double perovskite as a novel cathode material for CeO2- and LaGaO3-based solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: In this paper, we report the characteristics and applicability of a double perovskite NdBaCo2/3Fe2/3O5+delta (NBCFC) cathode on CeO2- and LaGaO3-based electrolytes.
Titulo: NdBaCo2/3Fe2/3Cu2/3O5+δ double perovskite as a novel cathode material for CeO2- and LaGaO3-based solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: NBCFC is found to crystallize in a tetragonal structure.
Titulo: NdBaCo2/3Fe2/3Cu2/3O5+δ double perovskite as a novel cathode material for CeO2- and LaGaO3-based solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Partial substitution of Fe and Cu for cobalt in NBCFC demonstrates significantly decreased TEC and good chemical compatibility with both Gd0.1Ce0.9O1.95 (GDC) and La0.9Sr0.1Ga0.8MgO3-delta (LSGM) electrolytes, while maintaining its good electrochemical performance.
Titulo: NdBaCo2/3Fe2/3Cu2/3O5+δ double perovskite as a novel cathode material for CeO2- and LaGaO3-based solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The oxidation states of transition metal cations are Co3+/Co4+, Fe3+/Fe4+, and Cu+/Cu2+, respectively.
Titulo: NdBaCo2/3Fe2/3Cu2/3O5+δ double perovskite as a novel cathode material for CeO2- and LaGaO3-based solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The average TEC of NBCFC is 15.7 x 10(-6) K-1 between 30 and 850 degrees C, and the polarization resistance values are 0.056 and 0.023 Omega cm(2) at 800 degrees C with GDC and LSGM electrolytes, respectively.
Titulo: NdBaCo2/3Fe2/3Cu2/3O5+δ double perovskite as a novel cathode material for CeO2- and LaGaO3-based solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The absence of spin-state transition in copper contributes to the TEC reduction.
Titulo: NdBaCo2/3Fe2/3Cu2/3O5+δ double perovskite as a novel cathode material for CeO2- and LaGaO3-based solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Addition of appropriate amounts of GDC into NBCFC to form NBCFC-GDC composite cathodes further reduce the TEC and improve cathode performance.
Titulo: NdBaCo2/3Fe2/3Cu2/3O5+δ double perovskite as a novel cathode material for CeO2- and LaGaO3-based solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: These results can be used to improve and develop novel double perovskite cathode materials.
Titulo: NdBaCo2/3Fe2/3Cu2/3O5+δ double perovskite as a novel cathode material for CeO2- and LaGaO3-based solid oxide fuel cells
